body_html:
Steps to reproduce:

  1. Create a file called demo.txt and add the following lines:
hi
ho
ha
  1. Run the following code:
import tensorflow as tf

table = tf.contrib.lookup.index_table_from_file('demo.txt')
s = tf.Session()
s.run(tf.tables_initializer())
s.run(tf.tables_initializer())

This will print something like
<DATE_OMITTED>: I tensorflow/core/kernels/lookup_util.cc:373] Table trying to initialize from file demo.txt is already initialized.

body:
Steps to reproduce:
1. Create a file called `demo.txt` and add the following lines:
```
hi
ho
ha
```
2. Run the following code:
```python
import tensorflow as tf

table = tf.contrib.lookup.index_table_from_file('demo.txt')
s = tf.Session()
s.run(tf.tables_initializer())
s.run(tf.tables_initializer())
```
This will print something like
`<DATE_OMITTED>: I tensorflow/core/kernels/lookup_util.cc:373] Table trying to initialize from file demo.txt is already initialized.`
